    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-26T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-26T07:00:00-05:00" n="632"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1078: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-26T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 26, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 26—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1025. Have just heard from Cadogan. Message that Sir Horace Wilson is taking to
                        Hitler<note n="79" xml:id="d632fn79">
                        <hi rend="italic">British Documents</hi>, 3d ser., vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ii</hi>, doc. No. 1097, p. 541.</note> is no agreement at all with
                    Hitler’s terms; it merely asks him to use reason and try to maintain
                    negotiations.</p>
                <p>The British and French have completely agreed to fight if Hitler makes any steps
                    after he turns down this proposition.</p>
                <p>They are very happy about the President’s message and they believe that the story
                    is now nearly finished and that they have made every effort to preserve peace.
                    If war comes they know they are going to get hell but they are now
                    reconciled.</p>
                <p>I am expecting to see Halifax within the next few minutes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
